Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro has rejected the plan, saying the effort is part of a broader attempt to overthrow his regime.
This comes as U.S. Vice President Mike Pence is scheduled to visit Colombia Monday to demand President Maduro step down.
This is certainly not some humanitarian aid; it’s a humanitarian intervention.
The fact that the United Nations and the Red Cross have both said they won’t work on this so-called humanitarian aid, because it is politically motivated, and that it is not humanitarian aid.
So, we have to confront this supposedly humanitarian aid, which is not humanitarian aid.